<figureCitation id="13592A1AFF848A757CB1FCB62B44FCBB" box="[752,855,822,849]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStartId-0="3.[170,203,1624,1646]" captionStartId-1="5.[170,203,1721,1743]" captionTargetBox-0="[231,1173,200,1595]" captionTargetBox-1="[347,1075,443,1675]" captionTargetId-0="figure-11@3.[211,1196,174,1615]" captionTargetId-1="figure-109@5.[248,1138,440,1716]" captionTargetPageId-0="3" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionText-0="Fig. 1–7. Line drawings of the Neoechinorhynchus (Neoechinorhynchus) agilis. 1 — Female, entire ventral view. 2 — Female reproductive system, papilla everted minimally. 3 — Male, entire view. 4 — Female reproductive system, papilla everted maximally. 5 — Posterior end of female in section, papilla everted maximally, cement cap is present. 6 — Eggs from the body cavity. 7— Female proboscis in section, hooks with root system." captionText-1="Fig. 8–11.Linedrawings ofthe syntypespecimens ofNeoechinorhynchus (Neoechinorhynchus) agilis. 8—Female proboscis. 9 — Female reproductive system. 10 — Hooks with root system. 11 — Female reproductive system." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453191" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453195" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6453191/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6453195/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="293">fig. 1–11</figureCitation>
